article.linkText: Pryor scores 19 in South Florida's 104-86 victory against Arkansas-Pine Bluff
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Kasean Pryor had 19 points in South Florida's 104-86 win over Arkansas-Pine Bluff on Tuesday night. Pryor also had six rebounds for the Bulls (4-4). Kobe Knox scored 18 points and added five assists. Sam Hines Jr. shot 4 of 7 from the field and 8 for 9 from the line to finish with 16 points, while adding eight rebounds and three steals. The Golden Lions (4-8) were led in scoring by Rashad Williams, who finished with 21 points and nine assists. Joe French added 17 points for UAPB. In addition, Jyre McCloud finished with 12 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
